{
  "text": "During preparation of this manuscript, an X-ray crystal structure of human AQP10 was published [CITATION_1] . To estimate the reliability of our homology models, we therefore aligned our homology model based on GlpF to this structure (PDB code 6F7H). We find good agreement of the position of selectivity filter residues between our model and the crystal structure (selectivity filter residues heavy atom RMSD = 0.71 \u00c5, see Fig. S1C ) and the discrepancy between the selectivity filter radii calculated by HOLE and cross-sectional areas calculated by SYBL are <10% in both cases; we therefore proceeded with our homology model for in silico analysis. The quality of our prediction of the AQP10 channel geometry also lends weight to our homology models of AQP3 and AQP9.",
